Pass 1H Pass 2C Pass 2NT Pass 3NT Pass 4NT Pass 6NT Pass Pass Pass
{South opens 1\H - how should you respond?
South rebids 2NT.  How do you continue?
North shows her minimum by bidding 3NT.
South continues with 4NT - what does this mean?  How do you continue?

 South's 4NT was not Blackwood, but rather a quantitative raise in Notrump, and an invitation to slam.
You have 15 points, and they are good ones. So you accept the invitation and bid 6NT.
There are 11 top tricks. A 3-3 \H split would provide the 12th winner, but this is against the odds. Better to try two \S finesses, a 75% chance.}

