Pass 1S Pass 2D Pass 2S Pass 4S Pass Pass Pass
{South opens 1\S -  
You responds 2\D, natural and game forcing.  South rebids 2\s.  In our style of 2/1, this promises 6+ cards in spades, and denies a side 4-card suit.  What should we bid now? 

You should jump to 4\S. This is Fast Arrival, indicating a minimum hand with no particular interest in slam.
South is happy to rest in the game contract.
Even with a combined 30 points, 10 tricks are certainly not a sure thing. South must hope that East holds the trump King.}

